To reproduce the numbers from the article, use the shell scripts provided in library/tools/interfaceScript.
In particular, the generateNumbers.sh script will run all experiments provided in the paper and write the 
results to the "results" folder in library/tools/interfaceScript. The outputs of the tools that we reference
in the paper can be found in the results-paper folder on the top-level of this supplementary material. 

We have run all tools on a machine with an Intel i5-4590 processor with 32GB of RAM that is running 
Ubuntu 14.04 (kernel 4.9.18). We used OpenJDK for Java 1.8.0_111 in its 64-Bit variant. 
NOTE: running the experiments with less than 32 GB of RAM leads to different results for Joana/JoDroid,
because for some samples, 32GB of RAM are required to analyze the samples.

Joana and JoDroid are included as source code and have to be built before running the tools. For
this, run "ant" in the folder material/joana.ui.wala.rifl10/. 
